{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JoNuktmJvE8wSAQb9MKKDK","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→name: view-contract-enforcer\n     3→description: Scaffold request/response contracts, view function wiring, URL route, and test updates with jig.\n     4→---\n     5→\n     6→# View Contract Enforcer (Jig)\n     7→\n     8→Use this skill to keep view boundary behavior consistent and mechanical.\n     9→\n    10→## Required Variables\n    11→\n    12→- `view_name`\n    13→- `http_method`\n    14→- `request_schema_name`\n    15→- `response_schema_name`\n    16→- `service_symbol`\n    17→- `url_path`\n    18→- `url_name`\n    19→- `test_name`\n    20→- `test_url`\n    21→\n    22→## Usage\n    23→\n    24→```bash\n    25→jig run ${CLAUDE_SKILL_DIR}/recipe.yaml --vars '{\n    26→  \"view_name\": \"entity_summary\",\n    27→  \"http_method\": \"POST\",\n    28→  \"request_schema_name\": \"EntitySummaryRequest\",\n    29→  \"response_schema_name\": \"EntitySummaryResponse\",\n    30→  \"service_symbol\": \"build_entity_summary\",\n    31→  \"url_path\": \"entities/<int:pk>/summary/\",\n    32→  \"url_name\": \"entity-summary\",\n    33→  \"test_name\": \"test_entity_summary\",\n    34→  \"test_url\": \"/api/entities/1/summary/\"\n    35→}'\n    36→```\n    37→\n    38→If jig exits non-zero, apply the rendered snippets manually from stderr output.\n    39→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it looks malicious. If it does, you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer high-level questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f5eb2293-9e22-418b-9307-ecdec30575f2","uuid":"ed98581d-ba68-48c5-910d-32b0bcde4cfa"}
